--- !u!114 &1836935252
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1836935251}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: c8fb21681af464c488715f87f9413a83, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueSystem
  siyahEkran: {fileID: 2050409254}
  butonlar: {fileID: 1775350610}
  dialogueText: {fileID: 2008684469}
  lines:
  - "Scene: Outside a small town library. Mid-afternoon.  NPC: Oh\u2014sorry! I didn't
    see you there.  MC: You almost stepped on my notebook.  NPC: ...I did?  MC: Your
    shoe stopped about three centimeters away. Approximately.  NPC: That's... oddly
    specific.  MC: I notice distances.  (A brief silence.)"
  - 'NPC: Well, thanks for not letting me destroy your notes.  MC: They aren''t notes. 
    NPC: No?  MC: They''re observations.  NPC: What''s the difference?'
  - 'MC: Notes are written to remember something. Observations are written so I don''t
    have to keep thinking about them.  NPC: Huh.  (The NPC smiles.)  NPC: I''m Alex.'
  - 'MC: ...  NPC: You don''t have to tell me your name if you don''t want to. MC:
    I wasn''t refusing. I was deciding.  NPC: Fair enough.  MC: It''s Rowan.  Alex:
    Nice to meet you, Rowan.  Rowan: You too.  (Another pause. Rowan glances away
    toward a passing bus.)  Alex: Is everything okay?'
  - 'Rowan: The bus brakes are loud.  Alex: Oh. Rowan: And the construction across
    the street. And someone''s phone is playing music.  Alex: That''s... a lot all
    at once.  Rowan: Usually people don''t hear all of it.  Alex: I guess I don''t. 
    (Alex notices Rowan gripping the notebook tightly.) '
  - '  Alex: Want to move somewhere quieter?  Rowan: Yes.  (Immediately.) Rowan:
    Thank you.  (They walk toward a nearby park.)  Alex: So... observations, huh? 
    Rowan: Yes.  Alex: What''s today''s observation?  Rowan: You apologized before
    making an excuse.  Alex: Is that unusual?'
  - "Rowan: More unusual than you'd think. Alex: Is that a compliment?  Rowan: It
    was intended as accurate.  (Alex laughs.)  Alex: I'll take accurate.  (For the
    first time, Rowan smiles\u2014just a little.)  Rowan: Most people don't."
